 TIMOTHY AGBOR, OSOGBO The Paramount ruler of Ijesaland, Oba Gabriel Adekunle Aromolaran has assured Osun State Governor, Gboyega Oyetola of Ijesa people’s votes during the July 16 governorship election. The traditional ruler of Ilesa, the hometown of the Minister of Interior, Rauf Aregbesola, gave this assurance on Wednesday when Oyetola visited his palace during his Strategic Engagement tour to the ancient. The governor sought for Aromolaran’s royal blessing ahead of the Saturday’s primary of the ruling All Progressives Congress and the gubernatorial poll. Speaking, Oba Aromolaran said, “Oyetola shall win governorship election for the second term. Anything I tell God, he answers it. You don’t need to waste your time soliciting votes in Ijesa because you already have our support. Your outstanding performance is obvious. You came for commissioning of this palace despite your busy schedule. “We can’t be an ingrate to you at the point you need our support, there is no other person to be voted for during 2022 Osun governorship election other than Oyetola. “We don’t give room for rascality in Ijesa land. The support we will give you includes peace. We have warned our wards that they should not get themselves involved in thuggery. “I pledge on behalf of the Ijesa people that we shall give your administration full support to ensure that you win come July 16, 2022. “Oyetola is so special to me. I always pray with my whole heart for our governor to be victorious. “Oyetola is the candidate that will win Ijesa land, whosoever opposes his candidature can smash his head on pole in Ijesa land. If they count the votes ten times, he will win against all odds. “I am not opposing any political party, but as far as I know, Oyetola will win Ijesa land because I am in full control of this land. “I admonish you to help Ijesa land with development and upgrade our college of Education to University. I thank you that you promise to think about it and feed us,” he said. 